      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Modern historians view the UN's effectiveness in stopping major wars in the 21st century as a qualified failure, though it has achieved some localized successes. While the Security Council has often been paralyzed by veto power, preventing decisive action in conflicts like Syria, the UN has been crucial in preventing outright global conflagrations. Its role in peacekeeping and humanitarian intervention has been vital, even if it hasn't always been able to stop the major conflicts themselves.",
